01:12:11.154 --> 01:12:14.954
green droplets are lipid droplets that we see in the

1216
01:12:14.994 --> 01:12:18.634
Tet2 knockout cells much more than in wild-type cells.

1217
01:12:18.674 --> 01:12:22.334
And in humans as well, using a different stain, you can see these lipid

1218
01:12:22.414 --> 01:12:24.974
droplets in Tet2-edited

1219
01:12:25.974 --> 01:12:29.234
HSCs, HSPCs, compared to wild type.

1220
01:12:29.654 --> 01:12:33.174
So there's a quite profound metabolic defect

1221
01:12:33.234 --> 01:12:36.554
related to lipid metabolism in these Tet2 knockout cells.

1222
01:12:38.354 --> 01:12:42.254
If you look by gene expression profiling in the Tet2 knockout cells

1223
01:12:42.314 --> 01:12:44.414
exposed to this inflammatory stimulus,

1224
01:12:45.434 --> 01:12:47.754
it's quite marked compared to wild-type cells.

1225
01:12:48.274 --> 01:12:48.974
But if you

1226
01:12:49.934 --> 01:12:53.634
knock out ACLY, one of the critical regulators, you

1227
01:12:53.754 --> 01:12:57.514
largely return the gene expression profile to the wild-type

1228
01:12:57.814 --> 01:12:58.034
state.

1229
01:13:01.154 --> 01:13:03.824
I mentioned that OGT was one of the other hits.

1230
01:13:04.434 --> 01:13:08.374
That struck us because OGT is one of the primary binding partners

1231
01:13:08.454 --> 01:13:11.724
of Tet2, and OGT is a regulator,

1232
01:13:12.394 --> 01:13:16.174
is actually a sensor of metabolic state in cells, and

1233
01:13:16.234 --> 01:13:18.294
it adds a sugar moiety,

1234
01:13:19.254 --> 01:13:22.954
glycan acylation, to many different proteins in the cell in

1235
01:13:23.014 --> 01:13:25.574
response to metabolic

1236
01:13:25.634 --> 01:13:29.412
stimuli.We tried to look at

1237
01:13:29.462 --> 01:13:33.022
that interaction between TET2 and OGT and map it.

1238
01:13:33.102 --> 01:13:34.002
We did a

1239
01:13:35.022 --> 01:13:38.922
base editing screen, tiling all of

1240
01:13:39.002 --> 01:13:42.982
TET2 and found some hits right where we predicted

1241
01:13:43.022 --> 01:13:45.822
the binding interaction between TET2 and OGT to be.

1242
01:13:47.802 --> 01:13:51.552
And then we developed a TR-FRET assay to look directly

1243
01:13:51.642 --> 01:13:53.742
at the interaction of the

1244
01:13:54.842 --> 01:13:58.592
TET2 with OGT right at this location, and you can

1245
01:13:58.722 --> 01:14:02.502
see there's a nice interaction here with wild type TET2

1246
01:14:02.562 --> 01:14:05.662
interacting with OGT. And if we mutate the critical

1247
01:14:06.302 --> 01:14:07.802
amino acids shown here,

1248
01:14:09.322 --> 01:14:12.482
we lose the interaction between TET2 and OGT.

1249
01:14:12.522 --> 01:14:16.122
So we think there's a very specific interaction that occurs at this locus between

1250
01:14:16.162 --> 01:14:19.502
TET2 and OGT. If TET2 is gone, OGT is

1251
01:14:19.862 --> 01:14:21.272
liberated from that interaction.

1252
01:14:22.642 --> 01:14:25.842
So there's a lot more to be worked out there, but we think

1253
01:14:25.902 --> 01:14:29.182
that TET2 mutations result in a

1254
01:14:29.802 --> 01:14:33.722
major metabolic defect and it's related to

1255
01:14:33.802 --> 01:14:37.722
OGT and its metabolic sensing. If you interrupt,

1256
01:14:38.342 --> 01:14:42.222
so if you knock out TET2, OGT is liberated from its

1257
01:14:42.242 --> 01:14:45.802
interaction with TET2, it results in

1258
01:14:45.862 --> 01:14:48.402
glyco-N-acylation that's aberrant.

1259
01:14:49.102 --> 01:14:52.742
It results in this lipid accumulation.

1260
01:14:52.822 --> 01:14:55.902
If you block AOLY, you remove that lipid

1261
01:14:56.762 --> 01:15:00.702
droplet formation. Lipid droplets are known to cause inflammation, and that,

1262
01:15:00.782 --> 01:15:04.242
again, can be inhibited by various inhibitors of lipid metabolism.

1263
01:15:04.902 --> 01:15:08.502
It also aligns with findings from our lab and a number of

1264
01:15:08.542 --> 01:15:12.162
labs that have shown mitochondrial

1265
01:15:12.202 --> 01:15:15.882
defects in TET2 knockout cells as well, which we think are

1266
01:15:15.902 --> 01:15:19.322
probably related to the substrates going into the mitochondria.

1267
01:15:21.572 --> 01:15:25.462
And then quickly, I just wanted to note prediction of outcome for CHIP,

1268
01:15:25.482 --> 01:15:28.882
because this is critical for us to think about how we are going to

1269
01:15:28.922 --> 01:15:32.422
