1282
01:16:14.662 --> 01:16:18.402
still, of course, increase the risk of

1283
01:16:18.412 --> 01:16:19.842
progression to myeloid malignancy.

1284
01:16:19.882 --> 01:16:23.402
It's just much smaller than the others, at least for the heterozygous

1285
01:16:23.862 --> 01:16:25.022
DNMT3A mutations.

1286
01:16:26.522 --> 01:16:30.452
By putting the various factors that we observed together, which are quite simple,

1287
01:16:31.142 --> 01:16:34.402
what the genotype is that's driving,

1288
01:16:35.122 --> 01:16:38.882
how many mutations are present, how big the clone is, RDW, which

1289
01:16:38.922 --> 01:16:42.442
in all studies have been very powerfully associated with

1290
01:16:42.842 --> 01:16:46.642
all the adverse outcomes, MCV, cytopenias, and age,

1291
01:16:47.022 --> 01:16:50.702
